'''Allan J. Katz''' (born 1947) is a former City Commissioner of [[Tallahassee]] and [[American people|American]] [[United States Ambassador to Portugal|Ambassador]] to Portugal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ambassador to Portugal: Who is Allan Katz|url=http://www.allgov.com/news/appointments-and-resignations/ambassador-to-portugal-who-is-allan-katz?news=840898|publisher=allgov.com|accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref> President Barack Obama nominated Allan to be Ambassador of the United States of America to the Portuguese Republic in November 2009. Ambassador Allan Katz is a distinguished professor with the University of Missouri Kansas City Bloch School's Department of Public Affairs and the College of Arts and Science's Political Science Department. He is the founder of the American Public Square, an organization using civil discourse to bridge the partisan divide. Allan is a lawyer by profession who has been active in local and national government and politics for many years. He has been a member of the Democratic National Committee where he helped draft the party's platform for the 2008 Democratic National Convention. Ambassador Katz holds a B.A. from the University of Missouri-Kansas City and a J.D. from the American University Washington College of Law in Washington D.C.<ref>http://americanpublicsquare.org/</ref> He was raised in a [[American Jews|Jewish]] family in [[St. Louis]], the son of Fred and Eileen Katz.<ref name=JewishLight>[http://www.stljewishlight.com/news/news_schmooze/article_acde3954-6882-11e1-aebb-0019bb2963f4.html St. Louis Jewish Light: "Local boys make good; Call for Unsung, brisket entries"] BY ELLEN FUTTERMAN] March 7, 2012</ref> His father escaped Nazi Germany for the United States where he worked as a salesman;<ref>[http://portugalresident.com/guests-touched-by-american-ambassador%E2%80%99s-revelation Portugal Resident: "Guests touched by American ambassador’s revelation" by Chris Graeme] July 09, 2010</ref> and was one of the original founders of the St. Louis Holocaust Museum.<ref name=JewishLight /> Katz graduated from University City High School.<ref name=JewishLight />

